## Memory Safety and Zeroisation
{{#if has_crypto}}

All types that hold cryptographic keys, passwords, tokens, or private key
material must actively zero their memory on drop.

```rust
use secrecy::Secret;
use zeroize::{Zeroize, ZeroizeOnDrop};

// Wrap sensitive values to prevent debug/display leakage
let api_key: Secret<String> = Secret::new(raw_key);

// Custom types holding secrets must derive ZeroizeOnDrop
#[derive(ZeroizeOnDrop)]
struct EncryptionKey {
    bytes: [u8; 32],
}
```

**Checklist:**
- [ ] All cryptographic keys use `ZeroizeOnDrop`
- [ ] Passwords and tokens wrapped in `secrecy::Secret`
- [ ] No sensitive values in plain `String` or `Vec<u8>` without a wrapper
- [ ] `Clone` implementations for sensitive types are also `ZeroizeOnDrop`
{{/if}}
