## Cryptographic Standards

### Algorithm Selection

| Use Case             | Required                       | Forbidden                      |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------ | ------------------------------ |
| Symmetric encryption | AES-256-GCM, ChaCha20-Poly1305 | AES-128, AES-ECB, RC4, 3DES    |
| Password hashing     | Argon2id                       | bcrypt alone, MD5, SHA-1       |
| Key exchange         | X25519                         | RSA < 4096, DH with known params |
| Digital signatures   | Ed25519                        | RSA-PKCS1, DSA                 |
| Random nonces        | `OsRng` (cryptographically secure) | `thread_rng`, timestamps   |

### Nonce Management

Never reuse a nonce with the same key. Generate a fresh random nonce for
every encryption operation.

```rust
use aes_gcm::{Aes256Gcm, KeyInit, aead::{Aead, OsRng, AeadCore}};

// CORRECT: Fresh random nonce every time
let nonce = Aes256Gcm::generate_nonce(&mut OsRng);
let ciphertext = cipher.encrypt(&nonce, plaintext)?;
// Store as: nonce || ciphertext
```

### Constant-Time Comparisons

All comparisons involving secrets must be constant-time:

```rust
use subtle::ConstantTimeEq;

// CORRECT
let is_valid = candidate_mac.ct_eq(&expected_mac).into();

// WRONG — leaks timing information
// let is_valid = candidate_mac == expected_mac;
```

