## Input Validation

Treat all external input as hostile — network data, files, environment
variables, FFI arguments, and CLI arguments.

```rust
// Validate at the boundary before the value enters the system
fn parse_and_validate(raw: &str) -> Result<ValidatedInput, ValidationError> {
    if raw.contains("..") {
        return Err(ValidationError::PathTraversal);
    }
    if raw.len() > MAX_INPUT_LEN {
        return Err(ValidationError::TooLong);
    }
    Ok(ValidatedInput(raw.to_string()))
}
```

Use the newtype pattern to enforce that validation has occurred:

```rust
pub struct ValidatedInput(String);  // Cannot be constructed without validation
```
